* {{ill|Kitsunezuka Kofun (Chichibu)|ja|狐塚古墳 (秩父市)|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Chichibu|ja|秩父市|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Saitama Prefecture|ja|埼玉県|qq=draft}}) - Circular kofun. * {{ill|Kitsunezuka Kofun (Setagaya)|ja|狐塚古墳 (世田谷区)|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Setagaya|ja|世田谷区|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Tokyo|ja|東京都|qq=draft}}) - Part of the {{ill|Ebaradai Kofun Cluster|ja|荏原台古墳群|qq=draft}}; circular kofun. * {{ill|Kitsunezuka Kofun (Chōfu)|ja|狐塚古墳 (調布市)|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Chōfu|ja|調布市|qq=draft}}, Tokyo) - Belongs to the Shimo-Fuda Kofun Cluster (Shimo-Fuda No. 6 Kofun). Designated as a Tokyo Metropolitan Historic Site. * {{ill|Toriibara Kitsunezuka Kofun|ja|鳥居原狐塚古墳|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Ichikawa Misato|ja|市川三郷町|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Yamanashi Prefecture|ja|山梨県|qq=draft}}) - Known for the excavation of the Akauru Gannen Mirror (Important Cultural Property). * {{ill|Kitsunezuka Kofun (Kyoto)|ja|狐塚古墳 (京都市)|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Ukyo Ward|ja|右京区|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Kyoto|ja|京都市|qq=draft}}). * Kitsunezuka Kofun (Sakai, Osaka) - Located in {{ill|Uenoshiba-chō|ja|上野芝町|qq=draft}}, Sakai; was an associated mound of the {{ill|Richūryō Kofun|ja|履中陵古墳|qq=draft}}, but no longer exists. * Nukatabe Kitsunezuka Kofun ({{ill|Yamatokōriyama|ja|大和郡山市|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Nara Prefecture|ja|奈良県|qq=draft}}) - A keyhole-shaped kofun part of the northern group of the {{ill|Mami Kofun Cluster|ja|馬見古墳群|1=Umami Kofun Cluster|qq=draft}}. * Samita Kitsunezuka Kofun ({{ill|Kawai|ja|河合町|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Kita Katsuragi District|ja|北葛城郡|qq=draft}}, Nara) - A scallop-shaped kofun in the central group of the Mami Kofun Cluster. * {{ill|Chihara Kitsunezuka Kofun|ja|茅原狐塚古墳|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Sakurai|ja|桜井市|qq=draft}}, Nara) - Known for its large stones. * Kitsunezuka Stone Sarcophagus ({{ill|Kakamigahara|ja|各務原市|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Gifu Prefecture|ja|岐阜県|qq=draft}}). * {{ill|Miyauchi Kitsunezuka Kofun|ja|宮内狐塚古墳|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Yurihama|ja|湯梨浜町|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Tottori Prefecture|ja|鳥取県|qq=draft}}). * Kitsunezuka Kofun (Itoshima) ({{ill|Itoshima|ja|糸島市|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Fukuoka Prefecture|ja|福岡県|qq=draft}}) - Part of the {{ill|Sone Archaeological Site Cluster|ja|曽根遺跡群|1=Sone Sites|qq=draft}}; a national historic site. * {{ill|Nakabaru Kitsunezuka Kofun|ja|中原狐塚古墳|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Kurume|ja|久留米市|qq=draft}}, Fukuoka) - An ornamental kofun within the {{ill|Tanushimaru Kofun Cluster|ja|田主丸古墳群|qq=draft}}; a national historic site. * {{ill|Kitsunezuka Kofun (Nichinan)|ja|狐塚古墳 (日南市)|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Nichinan|ja|日南市|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Miyazaki Prefecture|ja|宮崎県|qq=draft}}).
