{{afc comment|Wikidata entry [[d:Q11571377]] Wikidata name: (none) [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 07:35, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} {{afc comment|Wikidata entry [[d:Q11571377]] Wikidata name: (none) [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 04:14, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} '''Kitsunezuka Kofun''' (狐塚古墳) refers to various [[:en:Kofun|Kofun]] (ancient Kofuns) in Japan. These kofun share the same name and are found in different regions.
* {{ill|Kitsunezuka Kofun (Chichibu)|ja|狐塚古墳 (秩父市)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kitsunezuka Kofun (Chichibu)|qq=|1=kitsunezukakofun|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q17211528}} ([[:en:Chichibu, Saitama|Chichibu]], [[:en:Saitama Prefecture|Saitama Prefecture]]) - Circular kofun. * {{ill|Kitsunezuka Kofun (Setagaya)|ja|狐塚古墳 (世田谷区)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kitsunezuka Kofun (Setagaya)|qq=|1=Kitsunezuka Kofun|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q47633006}} ([[:en:Setagaya|Setagaya]], [[:en:Tokyo|Tokyo]]) - Part of the {{ill|Ebaradai Kofun Cluster|ja|荏原台古墳群|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ebaradai Kofun Cluster|qq=|1=Ebaradai kofun-gun|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11618305}}; circular kofun. * {{ill|Kitsunezuka Kofun (Chōfu)|ja|狐塚古墳 (調布市)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kitsunezuka Kofun (Chōfu)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} ([[:en:Chōfu|Chōfu]], Tokyo) - Belongs to the Shimo-Fuda Kofun Cluster (Shimo-Fuda No. 6 Kofun). Designated as a Tokyo Metropolitan Historic Site. * {{ill|Toriibara Kitsunezuka Kofun|ja|鳥居原狐塚古墳|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Toriibara Kitsunezuka Kofun|qq=}} ([[:en:Ichikawamisato|Ichikawa Misato]], [[:en:Yamanashi Prefecture|Yamanashi Prefecture]]) - Known for the excavation of the Akauru Gannen Mirror (Important Cultural Property). * {{ill|Kitsunezuka Kofun (Kyoto City)|lt=Kitsunezuka Kofun (Kyoto City)|lt=Kitsunezuka Kofun (Kyoto)|ja|狐塚古墳 (京都市)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kitsunezuka Kofun (Kyoto)|qq=}} ([[:en:Ukyō-ku, Kyoto|Ukyō-ku, Kyoto]], [[:en:Kyoto|Kyoto]]). * Kitsunezuka Kofun (Sakai, Osaka) - Located in {{ill|Uenoshiba-chō|ja|上野芝町|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Uenoshiba-chō|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, Sakai; was an associated mound of the {{ill|Richūryō Kofun|ja|履中陵古墳|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Richūryō Kofun|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|qid=Q135579711}}, but no longer exists. * Nukatabe Kitsunezuka Kofun ([[:en:Yamatokōriyama|Yamatokōriyama]], [[:en:Nara Prefecture|Nara Prefecture]]) - A keyhole-shaped kofun part of the northern group of the {{ill|Mami Kofun Cluster|ja|馬見古墳群|1=Umami Kofun Cluster|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mami Kofun Cluster|13=User:Immanuelle/Umami Kofun Cluster|qq=}}. * Samita Kitsunezuka Kofun ([[:en:Kawai, Nara|Kawai]], [[:en:Kitakatsuragi District, Nara|Kita Katsuragi District]], Nara) - A scallop-shaped kofun in the central group of the Mami Kofun Cluster. * {{ill|Chihara Kitsunezuka Kofun|ja|茅原狐塚古墳|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chihara Kitsunezuka Kofun|qq=|1=Chihara Kitsunezuka Kofun|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11617185}} ([[:en:Sakurai, Nara|Sakurai]], Nara) - Known for its large stones. * Kitsunezuka Stone Sarcophagus ([[:en:Kakamigahara|Kakamigahara]], [[:en:Gifu Prefecture|Gifu Prefecture]]). * {{ill|Miyauchi Kitsunezuka Kofun|ja|宮内狐塚古墳|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Miyauchi Kitsunezuka Kofun|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} ([[:en:Yurihama, Tottori|Yurihama]], [[:en:Tottori Prefecture|Tottori Prefecture]]). * Kitsunezuka Kofun (Itoshima) ([[:en:Itoshima, Fukuoka|Itoshima]], [[:en:Fukuoka Prefecture|Fukuoka Prefecture]]) - Part of the [[:en:Sone Sites|Sone Sites]]; a national historic site. * {{ill|Nakabaru Kitsunezuka Kofun|ja|中原狐塚古墳|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nakabaru Kitsunezuka Kofun|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} ([[:en:Kurume|Kurume]], Fukuoka) - An ornamental kofun within the {{ill|Tanushimaru Kofun Cluster|ja|田主丸古墳群|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tanushimaru Kofun Cluster|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}; a national historic site. * {{ill|Kitsunezuka Kofun (Nichinan)|ja|狐塚古墳 (日南市)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kitsunezuka Kofun (Nichinan)|qq=|1=Kitsunezuka Kofun (Nichinan)|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q128307755}} ([[:en:Nichinan, Miyazaki|Nichinan]], [[:en:Miyazaki Prefecture|Miyazaki Prefecture]]).
