okōriyama|Yamatokōriyama]], [[:en:Nara Prefecture|Nara Prefecture]]) - A keyhole-shaped kofun part of the northern group of the {{ill|Mami Kofun Cluster|ja|馬見古墳群|1=Umami Kofun Cluster|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mami Kofun Cluster|13=User:Immanuelle/Umami Kofun Cluster|qq=}}. * Samita Kitsunezuka Kofun ([[:en:Kawai, Nara|Kawai]], [[:en:Kitakatsuragi District, Nara|Kita Katsuragi District]], Nara) - A scallop-shaped kofun in the central group of the Mami Kofun Cluster. * {{ill|Chihara Kitsunezuka Kofun|ja|茅原狐塚古墳|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chihara Kitsunezuka Kofun|qq=|1=Chihara Kitsunezuka Kofun|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11617185}} ([[:en:Sakurai, Nara|Sakurai]], Nara) - Known for its large stones. * Kitsunezuka Stone Sarcophagus ([[:en:Kakamigahara|Kakamigahara]], [[:en:Gifu Prefecture|Gifu Prefecture]]). * {{ill|Miyauchi Kitsunezuka Kofun|ja|宮内狐塚古墳|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Miyauchi Kitsunezuka Kofun|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|qid=Q135579712}} ([[:en:Yurihama, Tottori|Yurihama]], [[:en:Tottori Prefecture|Tottori Prefecture]]). * Kitsunezuka Kofun (Itoshima) ([[:en:Itoshima, Fukuoka|Itoshima]], [[:en:Fukuoka Prefecture|Fukuoka Prefecture]]) - Part of the [[:en:Sone Sites|Sone Sites]]; a national historic site. * {{ill|Nakabaru Kitsunezuka Kofun|ja|中原狐塚古墳|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nakabaru Kitsunezuka Kofun|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|qid=Q135579713}} ([[:en:Kurume|Kurume]], Fukuoka) - An ornamental kofun within the {{ill|Tanushimaru Kofun Cluster|ja|田主丸古墳群|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tanushimaru Kofun Cluster|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}; a national historic site. * {{ill|Kitsunezuka Kofun (Nichinan)|ja|狐塚古墳 (日南市)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kitsunezuka Kofun (Nichinan)|qq=|1=Kitsunezuka Kofun (Nichinan)|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q128307755}} ([[:en:Nichinan, Miyazaki|Nichinan]], [[:en:Miyazaki Prefecture|Miyazaki Prefecture]]).
